# PR Review Rules

## Code Quality Checklist

When reviewing pull requests, check the following:

### TypeScript & Type Safety
- No use of `any` without justification in a comment
- All new public functions have explicit return types
- No type assertions (`as`) without a comment explaining why it's safe
- New interfaces/types are placed in appropriate `dto/` or `entities/` files

### Error Handling
- All async operations have proper error handling (try/catch or .catch())
- NestJS endpoints use appropriate HTTP status codes
- Bot communication errors are handled gracefully (timeouts, retries)
- Database operations use transactions where multi-step writes occur

### Security
- No secrets or credentials hardcoded (use ConfigService / env vars)
- User input is validated using class-validator decorators on DTOs
- SQL queries use parameterized inputs (no string concatenation)
- JWT tokens are properly validated in protected routes
- Rate limiting is applied to public endpoints

### Testing
- New features include unit tests at minimum
- Critical game logic changes include integration tests
- Test files follow the naming convention: `*.spec.ts` or `*.test.ts`
- Tests are placed in the correct directory: `tests/unit/`, `tests/integration/`, or `tests/e2e/`
- Coverage thresholds are met (80% statements, branches, functions, and lines)

### Game Engine Integrity
- Poker hand evaluation logic changes must have comprehensive edge-case tests
- Betting round changes must account for all-in scenarios and side pots
- Tournament state changes must handle concurrent table operations
- Card shuffling must use the provably-fair seed system

### Database & Migrations
- New entities have corresponding migration files
- Migration timestamps must be greater than all existing migrations
- Migrations include both `up()` and `down()` methods
- Schema changes are backwards-compatible or have a migration plan

### Performance
- No N+1 query patterns in repository methods
- Large result sets use pagination
- WebSocket events are not emitted more frequently than necessary
- Game state snapshots are appropriately sized

### Code Style
- ESLint passes without errors (`npm run lint:check`)
- Prettier formatting is applied (`npm run format:check`)
- No commented-out code blocks merged
- Imports are organized (NestJS decorators, then external, then internal)
